news.title: Punjab cabinet approves land pooling policy
news.para: Under this policy, land owners can give their land either to the state government or a builder or they can develop the land on their own, he said.

news.title: Emaar India to invest ₹400 crore to develop residential project in Lucknow
news.para: Developed on 2.923 acres of land, the project offers a wide range of residential units, 3BHK + U and 4BHK + U (two types).

news.title: Gujarat government's new policy to enable cross-city transferable development rights
news.para: The policy framework proposes an inter-city TDR framework, allowing cross-city transfer of development rights in Ahmedabad, Surat, Vadodara, Rajkot and other urban centres while addressing various urban challenges.

news.title: Bhubaneswar civic body to set up three more ODA courts to resolve building plan disputes
news.para: At present, there is only one ODA court that deals with thousands of minor and major disputes, creating a huge backlog. An estimated 7,000 disputes are pending for disposal, BMC officials said.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body collects over ₹2,400 crore in property tax in Apr-May 2025
news.para: As of May 30, property tax collections stood at Rs 598.51 crore in Mahadevapura, Rs 455.06 crore in the East Zone, Rs 391.96 crore in the South Zone, Rs 270.36 crore in the West Zone, Rs 258.63 crore in Bommanahalli, Rs 197.97 crore in Yelahanka, Rs 175.27 crore in RR Nagar, and Rs 77.17 crore in Dasarahalli.

news.title: NBCC defends bulk sale of new Amrapali flats to private builders
news.para: NBCC chairperson and managing director KP Mahadevaswamy, however, maintained that the decision was necessary given the severe financial constraints.

news.title: Illegal construction begins at sector 17 collapsed building site, Chandigarh DC orders probe
news.para: While the debris of the collapsed building was cleared from the site a few days back, multiple iron columns have now come up at the spot despite the fact that the UT estate office has not approved a revised building plan for the site so far.

news.title: Karnataka HC orders demolition of illegal building, recovery of costs from BBMP officials
news.para: The case centres around a residential building at Nanjundeshwara Layout, which local residents alleged was coming up without an approved building plan.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires 14-acre land parcel in Pune
news.para: The development on this land will comprise primarily premium group housing. The project will have a developable potential of 3.7 million sq ft with an estimated revenue potential of ₹4,200 crore.

news.title: Delhi civic body makes user charge optional for property tax payments from June 1
news.para: This move aims to resolve confusion that had prevented many from paying their taxes in advance and allows taxpayers to continue availing a 10% discount on early payments, valid until June 30.

news.title: Kochi metro phase II moves ahead with tender for five more stations
news.para: These stations will be built along the JLN Stadium–Kakkanad corridor at Palarivattom bypass, Padamugal, Vazhakkala, Chembumukku, and Alinchuvadu.

news.title: Asian Development Bank commits $10 billion plan for India's urban transformation
news.para: ADB is also committing USD 3 million in technical assistance to design bankable projects and strengthen the capacity of states and urban local bodies, it said.

news.title: Help desk for online registration of vacant Prayagraj development body's flats
news.para: These flats cater to various categories, including EWS, LIG, 1BHK, 2BHK, and 3BHK, and will be allocated through a lottery system, providing a fair opportunity to prospective buyers.

news.title: Survey to check impact of land acquisition for Noida airport phase 3 & 4
news.para: Two runways and a global aerospace manufacturing hub are proposed on 2,053 hectares—of which 1,857 hectares are privately owned and will be acquired from 14 villages—in two of the four-phase development of the airport.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body collects ₹60 crore property tax during two-month rebate period
news.para: The final figures might increase slightly, but this collection marks the highest amount ever received during a two-month rebate period.

news.title: Maharashtra: Housing societies raise redevelopment and maintenance issues in feedback to draft rules
news.para: The draft rules, which have been pending since the Act was amended in 2019, were published on April 15, following which state govt invited feedback by May 15.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body set to proceed after getting estate office’s nod on freehold
news.para: Meanwhile, the Chandigarh Housing Board (CHB) informed the MC that they do not engage in activities involving the disposal of chunks of land.

news.title: Over 40 Noida societies lack pollution board nod to operate STPs
news.para: It permits industries, commercial establishments, and group housing societies to operate their facilities while ensuring that their emissions, effluents, and waste management systems comply with environmental standards.

news.title: Property registrations in Mumbai decline 4% to 11,565 in May 2025
news.para: While property registrations declined by 4% year-on-year in May 2025, stamp duty collection witnessed a rise of 3% during the same period.

news.title: Over 2,600 real estate projects expire in Karnataka, many more lapse: RERA data
news.para: A significant number of real estate projects failed to meet their deadlines, with over 2,600 officially marked as ‘expired' and more than 2,700 classified as ‘lapsed', as per latest K-Rera data.
